<$fill $name="body">

!! What it does

''kind'' is a lightweight schema engine for TiddlyWiki. Each type's full definition ‚Äî fields, constraints, title formula, icon, namespace memberships, and stream-river display config ‚Äî lives on a single tiddler. Instances are plain tiddlers marked with a `kind.type` field. No inheritance, no separate per-field tiddlers, no central registry.

!! Features

* ''Schema-as-tiddler'' ‚Äî one tiddler per type, with field defs as a JSON array in `kind.fields`
* ''Discovery'' ‚Äî `[all[shadows+tiddlers]has[kind.type]has[kind.fields]]` finds all type tiddlers
* ''Namespaces'' ‚Äî types declare `kind.namespaces`, the active scope picks one (or all)
* ''Editor'' ‚Äî 2-column form (label + input), table-style, with live validation messages
* ''Field Bar'' ‚Äî auto-rendered in the stream river on every instance; configurable per type; self-disabling
* ''Creator'' ‚Äî pick a type, fill fields, click Create; title computed from `kind.title-formula`
* ''Validator'' ‚Äî wiki-wide report of constraint violations
* ''Type-builder'' ‚Äî structured editor for type metadata + JSON textarea for fields, with live preview

!! Schema model

* ''Type tiddlers'' ‚Äî fields `kind.type` (the key), `kind.caption`, `kind.icon`, `kind.namespaces`, `kind.title-formula`, `kind.stream-fields`, and `kind.fields` (JSON array)
* ''Field defs'' ‚Äî entries inside the JSON array with `key`, `typed`, `caption`, `icon`, `constraints`, `options` (enum), `ref-types` + `cardinality` (ref)
* ''Instance tiddlers'' ‚Äî any tiddler with `kind.type: <type-key>` is an instance

!! Prerequisites

TiddlyWiki ‚â• 5.4.0 in Node.js server mode. No other plugin dependencies. Optional: `$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template` for the documentation hub you're reading right now.

!! Quick start

# Open the ''type-builder'' tab; create a blank type and fill its metadata
# Paste a field-list JSON (see the Examples section)
# Open the ''creator'' tab, pick the type, fill the fields, click Create
# Open the resulting tiddler in the story river ‚Äî the field bar appears at the top
# Use the ''validator'' tab to scan the whole wiki for constraint violations

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="info">
<$fill $name="body">''Why a new plugin alongside `rimir/typed`?'' typed has accumulated features (3-level inheritance, separate per-field tiddlers, two ref-editor modes, ~1600 lines). kind drops everything that doesn't pay rent in TiddlyWiki's bag-of-fields model and adds namespaces. See the FAQ for details.</$fill>
</$transclude>

